body:
I am using verilator to create a binary executable of our system verilog design . We are running into some errors on the cpp files generated.  Please find one such example below 

 

 

**ERROR : Vmod_sram_wrapper__DepSet_h01a03603__0__Slow.cpp:103:46: error: request for member \u2018__PVT__BIST\u2019 in \u2018vlSelf->Vmod_sram_wrapper:`_i_ram_mbist`_[7]\u2019, which is of non-class type \u2018CData\u2019 {aka \u2018unsigned char\u2019}
  103 |                                         [7U].__PVT__BIST))));**


Here the tool is inferring structure instance` i_ram_mbist` is of type character rather than class/struct type.

 

 This structure is defined as a package :-

```
package dft_mbist;

  typedef struct   {
    logic         BIST;
    logic [38:0]  WEB; // MBIST bit write enable
    logic         CEB;
  } t_i_mbist_top_mem;

endpackage
```

In our system Verilog RTL , this structure is instantiated as:-

 

```
 import dft_mbist::*;

 input      t_i_mbist_top_mem i_ram_mbist [7:0];

mem_wrapper  wrapper_0(

.bist_0 (i_ram_mbist[0].MBIST);

.bist_1(i_ram_mbist[1].MBIST);

.bist_2(i_ram_mbist[2].MBIST);
.

.

.

.

);
```

 

**Verilator command used :- Verilator - --binary -j 0 -Wall --timescale 1ps/1fs --bbox-unsup --bbox-sys --assert --Wpedantic -sv -Wno-lint -Wno-style -Wno-BLKANDNBLK -Wno-BLKLOOPINIT -Wno-MULTIDRIVEN -Wno-UNOPTFLAT -Wno-COMBDLY -Wno-NOLATCH +systemverilogext+  -Wno-EOFNEWLINE -Wno-style -Wno-lint -f  <file_list.f>  -top top_module** 

 



****Verilator version :- Verilator 5.027 devel rev v5.026-2-gd5cfe1a**

**GCC version:-gcc (GCC) 7.3.0****
